# Default mirror, pre-selected by the Klyx bootstrap build.
#
# Without an explicit entry here, the upstream `pkg` script in
# `termux-tools` treats sources.list as "unselected" on first
# `apt update` / `pkg install`, kicks off its auto-probe over a
# rotating candidate list, and writes whichever mirror responded
# fastest to a curl `HEAD`. That probe is a false-positive on
# mirrors with bot-protection CDNs (e.g. mirror.textcord.xyz),
# which return HTTP 200 on the bot-check page but serve HTML
# instead of clearsigned PGP for InRelease, so apt then fails
# with `Clearsigned file isn't valid, got 'NOSPLIT'`.
#
# Hard-coding packages.termux.dev (the official Termux mirror)
# keeps `pkg` from auto-probing, gives users a deterministic
# starting point, and lets them switch via `termux-change-repo`
# if they want a different CDN.
deb https://packages.termux.dev/apt/termux-main stable main
